<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="378" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">de Margerie</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-31"><hi rend="italic">July 31,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 492.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with the request contained
                            in your note of the 24th instant, it has given me pleasure to make known
                            to the persons named in your note that the Government of the French
                            Republic thanks them for such assistance as they rendered to the
                            sufferers from the recent volcanic eruption in Martinique.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>